      • tokenize

        public void tokenize​(java.lang.String str)
        Tokenize(str) takes in a string to be turned into tokens. It sets a default flag value (match) to false then for each possible token in the string, it sees if the token currently being looked at is a match to any of the regex's stored in the tokenizer if it is, the flag is switched to true the token is added to the token LinkedList, it's is replaced by the "" character,leading whitespace is trimmed and the next token is evaluated if it doesn't match, an exception is raised and tells the console what unexpected value appeared
        Parameters:
        str - the str
